info.description:
This document gives an overview on all the REST services that are available for the ProSoccerData Club API.
### How to use the Club API?
#### Authentication
To authenticate to the API, add the API Keys you received in the header of each request you make to the API.
#### API Keys
ProSoccerData's Club API supports the use of API Keys. API Keys allow you to use another method of authentication separate from your account username and password. 
API Keys add an additional layer of security for your account and can be assigned to limit which areas of your account they may be used to access. 
To use keys, you must set some plain text headers:
* x-api-club: &lt;Club Key&gt;
* x-api-key: &lt;API Key&gt;
* Authorization: bearer &lt;API Secret&gt;

##### Example header
> GET https://clubapi.prosoccerdata.com/teams HTTP/1.1<br/>
> x-api-club: &lt;Club Key&gt;<br/>
> x-api-key: &lt;API Key&gt;<br/>
> Authorization: &lt;API Secret&gt;

> curl -X "GET" "https://clubapi.prosoccerdata.com/teams" -H "Authorization: bearer &lt;API Secret&gt;" -H "x-api-club: &lt;Club Key&gt;" -H "x-api-key: &lt;API Key&gt;" -H "Content-Type: application/json"

#### Authorization
The API Keys are used to authenticate to the Club API.  The permissions that are available to the API Keys are assigned with the user that is linked
to the API Key.  The user is a regular user that can be created within the club platform.  This can be a real staff member, or can be fictive user
that has been created specifically for the API.  Either way, the club admin can set the necessary permissions for this user through "Control Panel -> Rights"
and limit the possibilities of the API.

**Important:** the club admin MUST select a platform user, otherwise the API will not be able to authenticate.

#### API Limitations
At the moment, you are not allowed to use the Club API on your website directly.  You will have to make sure that you implement a
synchronization mechanism which fetches the data from the API into your own backend system and show the data from your own
database.

The limits for the API calls are the following:
* Max requests per day: 2000
* Max requests per second: 5
